HEADWORD: Anticyclone
<hw>An"ti*cy`clone</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧*s⟦imac⟧`kl⟦omac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Meteorol.)</fld> <def>A movement of the atmosphere
opposite in character, as regards direction of the wind and distribution
of barometric pressure, to that of a cyclone.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>An`ti*cy*clon"ic</wf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> --
<wf>An`ti*cy*clon"ic*al*ly</wf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

